quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Increment Operator[/h1]

For example: [code format="cpp" codeId="190"]int x = 11;
x++;
cout << x;

//Outputs 12[/code]

[h1]Increment Operator[/h1]

The increment operator has two forms, [b]prefix [/b]and [b]postfix[/b].[b][/b][code format="cpp"]++x; //prefix
x++; //postfix[/code]
[b]Prefix [/b]increments the value, and then proceeds with the expression. 
[b]Postfix [/b]evaluates the expression and then performs the incrementing.

[b]Prefix example:[/b] [code format="cpp"]x = 5;
y = [b]++x[/b];
// x is 6, y is 6[/code]
[b]Postfix example:[/b] [code format="cpp"]x = 5;
y = [b]x++[/b];
// x is 6, y is 5[/code]
[note]The [b]prefix [/b]example increments the value of x, and then assigns it to y.
The [b]postfix [/b]example assigns the value of x to y, and then increments it.[/note]

